Interior cabinet secretary Fred Matiang'i, his health Counterpart Mutahi Kagwe and education's George Magoha Today held a consultative forum with religious leaders on The safety protocols in places of worship. Today's meeting Was the culmination of a week?long series of engagements As directed by the president. The recommendations of Today's meeting will be presented to the president who Will issue communication on the way forward. There has  Been increased pressure to open up places of worship Since they were ordered shut on March 22 due to the Coronavirus pandemic.